<br>
You then proceed to talk about how you were never addicted to Everquest and how easy it was for you to quit.  A question immediately popped into my head.  If this is guy is so over Everquest and obviously has so many better things to do with his time, why does he keep posting on these boards?  He seems to imply that his life has all of the sudden become very interesting and yet he still finds the time to post on the message boards.<br>
<br>
To the extent that playing Everquest and any related addiction can be considered pathetic, I wonder if not playing Everquest anymore yet having the need to come to an Everquest-related message board to remind those that do play how pathetic they are and how much better your life is now can be considered more pathetic.<br>
